1
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,300
<i>This is the only way I can get
into the Torrecampos' world.</i>

2
00:00:12,433 --> 00:00:14,900
<i> We regained the Orbos account.</i>

3
00:00:15,033 --> 00:00:17,567
<i>Looks like we found ourselves a
new lucky charm in this company.</i>

4
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:18,500
<i> You look pale.</i>

5
00:00:18,633 --> 00:00:19,733
<i> Marj, you're bleeding.</i>

6
00:00:19,867 --> 00:00:21,167
<i>We need to get you
to the hospital.</i>

7
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:22,133
<i> Almost three months.</i>

8
00:00:22,267 --> 00:00:23,533
<i>Congratulations,
Mrs. Torrecampo.</i>

9
00:00:23,667 --> 00:00:26,700
<i>I don't know if I'm ready
to forget what happened...</i>

10
00:00:26,833 --> 00:00:27,833
<i> but thank you.</i>

11
00:00:27,967 --> 00:00:30,433
<i>Don't worry about work.
I'll take care of Paolo.</i>

12
00:00:30,567 --> 00:00:31,433
<i> I'll take care of everything.</i>

13
00:00:31,567 --> 00:00:32,667
<i>Leave Paolo alone.
He's a grown man.</i>

14
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,667
<i>Exactly. You picked
the wrong Torrecampo to date.</i>

15
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:36,200
<i> Is it too late?</i>

16
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:40,300
<i>If blessings come to me
on their own, I won't say no.</i>

17
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:44,533
<i>Marj, make sure you eat well,
okay?</i>

18
00:00:44,667 --> 00:00:45,767
You know, sweetheart,

19
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:48,567
I had my friend Ekang cook
that shrimp paste just for you.

20
00:00:50,667 --> 00:00:53,267
Make her eat lots of vegetables.

21
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:55,533
The ones that help the baby
hold on tight.

22
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:57,267
The healthy stuff.

23
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,867
Mom, this is too much food.

24
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,667
I know that chicken soup
is your favorite.

25
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:04,867
- Eat up.
- Okay.

26
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,167
My grandchild's almost
seven months now.

27
00:01:09,467 --> 00:01:12,867
How's Paolo, by the way?

28
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,233
He must be excited, right?

29
00:01:17,033 --> 00:01:18,000
It's nothing, Mom.

30
00:01:18,133 --> 00:01:20,533
But I just feel
a little guilty lately.

31
00:01:21,267 --> 00:01:22,967
It's been a while since we've...

32
00:01:25,533 --> 00:01:26,567
you know.

33
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:29,167
The doctor said
it's not allowed.

34
00:01:30,533 --> 00:01:33,733
Sweetheart, you have nothing
to worry about.

35
00:01:34,067 --> 00:01:35,733
You shouldn't feel guilty.

36
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:38,533
There's nothing
to be ashamed of.

37
00:01:39,367 --> 00:01:43,100
All you're thinking about
is the baby's safety.

38
00:01:43,267 --> 00:01:45,200
There's nothing wrong with that.

39
00:01:46,133 --> 00:01:47,267
I know, Mom.

40
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:53,867
But sometimes I feel like Paolo
thinks I'm pushing him away.

41
00:01:54,633 --> 00:01:57,067
It feels like things
between us are getting cold.

42
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:59,267
Oh, Marj.

43
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,167
You know how men are sometimes.

44
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:05,367
They don't know how to adjust.

45
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,933
But if you want
to make it up to him,

46
00:02:11,433 --> 00:02:16,633
there are other ways
to show you love him.

47
00:02:18,467 --> 00:02:22,167
Just take care of yourself,
okay?

48
00:02:22,667 --> 00:02:29,267
If there's trust and care,
the spark won't disappear.

49
00:02:33,567 --> 00:02:36,100
Look at that belly, so big
already. It's almost time.

50
00:02:36,233 --> 00:02:37,933
I'm so excited.

51
00:02:38,067 --> 00:02:39,233
<i> Mom, he kicked!</i>

52
00:02:39,367 --> 00:02:41,133
<i> Oh! I felt it!</i>

53
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,067
Didn't I tell the three
of you

54
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:30,300
to double-check the figures
before sending them?

55
00:03:30,433 --> 00:03:31,733
What is this?

56
00:03:31,867 --> 00:03:33,133
Another mistake?

57
00:03:33,267 --> 00:03:35,100
Didn't we learn anything
last quarter?

58
00:03:35,467 --> 00:03:37,933
- Sir, I thought...
- Thought what?

59
00:03:38,067 --> 00:03:39,667
You can't keep assuming!

60
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:42,300
We're still recovering
from losses!

61
00:03:42,433 --> 00:03:43,733
Fix it!

62
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:46,800
<i> He just picked on you, Bro.</i>

63
00:03:46,933 --> 00:03:48,133
Not your fault.

64
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,400
Maybe Sir Paolo's just
not getting any.

65
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,500
His wife's off-limits, right?

66
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:55,467
Delicate pregnancy and all.

67
00:03:55,733 --> 00:03:56,900
<i> Isn't that what happens</i>

68
00:03:57,033 --> 00:03:58,300
<i>when a man doesn't
have an outlet at home?</i>

69
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:00,200
What did you say?

70
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:04,133
Sir, it was just a joke, Sir.

71
00:04:04,267 --> 00:04:05,467
A joke to you?

72
00:04:06,067 --> 00:04:08,933
I'm protecting my wife.

73
00:04:09,067 --> 00:04:10,233
That's a joke?

74
00:04:11,767 --> 00:04:12,600
Pack your things.

75
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:13,767
You're done.

76
00:04:14,667 --> 00:04:15,400
Sir...

77
00:04:16,033 --> 00:04:17,567
What, are you going
to report me to HR?

78
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:19,867
Good. Do it.
I'll report you, too.

79
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,233
I'm not scared.

80
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:22,667
Pack your things.

81
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,067
You're fired!

82
00:04:25,633 --> 00:04:27,833
You fired one of your staff

83
00:04:28,767 --> 00:04:30,367
because he called you
sexually frustrated?

84
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,400
Dad, he was disrespectful!

85
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:36,233
He said something about Marj.

86
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:40,167
I couldn't just let it slide.

87
00:04:41,133 --> 00:04:43,533
Well, if your wife
won't give it to you,

88
00:04:44,233 --> 00:04:45,700
what do you expect?

89
00:04:46,433 --> 00:04:48,533
No wonder you've been
in a bad mood, son.

90
00:04:49,267 --> 00:04:52,233
Dad, you don't understand.

91
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:54,767
Marj's pregnancy is sensitive.

92
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,567
We have to be careful.

93
00:04:59,933 --> 00:05:01,267
So that's it?

94
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:05,400
If you can't have it at home,
find it outside.

95
00:05:06,067 --> 00:05:07,300
Simple.

96
00:05:08,633 --> 00:05:10,600
That's your advice?

97
00:05:11,667 --> 00:05:13,467
If I can't get it from my wife,

98
00:05:14,667 --> 00:05:16,000
<i> I should find someone else?</i>

99
00:05:16,633 --> 00:05:17,567
Son...

100
00:05:18,433 --> 00:05:20,667
if you're not releasing
that tension at work,

101
00:05:21,267 --> 00:05:25,867
where else is it going?

102
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:28,567
There's nothing wrong with it.

103
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:29,967
Just be discreet.

104
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:33,067
What Marj doesn't know
won't hurt her.

105
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:35,867
Dad, please.

106
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:39,267
I'm not that person anymore.

107
00:05:39,667 --> 00:05:41,633
Okay? I'm married.

108
00:05:43,433 --> 00:05:44,433
I don't want to fight with her,

109
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:46,833
and I definitely don't want
to break her trust.

110
00:05:47,567 --> 00:05:48,400
Trust?

111
00:05:50,467 --> 00:05:52,500
Trust is overrated, Paolo.

112
00:05:52,933 --> 00:05:54,467
Don't let marriage
hold you back.

113
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:59,167
Power and peace of mind.
That's what you need.

114
00:05:59,867 --> 00:06:01,467
Learn how to balance.

115
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:06,667
If that's your definition
of balance...

116
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:08,333
Dad, pass.

117
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:11,233
Don't act so holy, son.

118
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:15,767
We all have needs...

119
00:06:17,067 --> 00:06:20,033
our chosen partners
can't always meet.

120
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:23,967
The sooner you accept that,

121
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,300
the easier life gets.

122
00:06:30,533 --> 00:06:31,733
I'll get going.

123
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:42,000
Yolly.

124
00:06:42,167 --> 00:06:43,867
- Yes, Ma'am?
- Make sure the adobo

125
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:47,367
has extra sauce.
Paolo loves it that way.

126
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:48,967
- Yes, Ma'am.
- And, Weng?

127
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:50,000
Yes, Ma'am?

128
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:53,367
Can you tone down the sourness
of the sinigang?

129
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:55,400
I don't want him
getting acid reflux.

130
00:06:55,933 --> 00:06:58,833
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Wow, this looks like a fiesta.

131
00:06:58,967 --> 00:07:01,700
It does, Yolly.
Sir Paolo's so lucky.

132
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:04,433
Ma'am Marj's planning
a romantic dinner.

133
00:07:04,567 --> 00:07:07,900
It's just been a while
since we've had a date.

134
00:07:08,033 --> 00:07:11,233
I just want him to feel
how much I love him,

135
00:07:11,367 --> 00:07:13,500
even if other things
aren't allowed yet.

136
00:07:15,300 --> 00:07:16,700
- Rose, Cathy...
- Yes, Ma'am?

137
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,933
Help them out, okay? Please.

138
00:07:19,067 --> 00:07:21,367
I'll set the table.

139
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:23,300
Excuse me.

140
00:07:44,333 --> 00:07:46,100
- Love?
- Hi, Love.

141
00:07:46,233 --> 00:07:48,300
Are you coming home
for dinner tonight?

142
00:07:48,733 --> 00:07:49,867
I can. Why?

143
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,067
<i> Nothing.</i>

144
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:53,233
I cooked all your favorites.

145
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:55,067
<i> I'll wait for you.</i>

146
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:56,700
Love...

147
00:07:57,333 --> 00:07:59,733
you might get tired.
You don't have to.

148
00:07:59,867 --> 00:08:01,067
I want to.

149
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:04,000
So please,
please come home early.

150
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:06,833
Okay.

151
00:08:06,967 --> 00:08:08,033
I'll be there.

152
00:08:09,067 --> 00:08:10,000
Marj...

153
00:08:10,767 --> 00:08:13,533
<i>- I love you.
-I love you so much, too, Paolo.</i>

154
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,433
- See you later.
- See you.

155
00:08:16,967 --> 00:08:17,933
Bye.

156
00:08:33,633 --> 00:08:36,033
Sorry, Paolo, this is urgent.

157
00:08:36,167 --> 00:08:37,567
The country manager

158
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:40,833
of NextConnect Global Services
messaged me.

159
00:08:40,967 --> 00:08:43,133
He's willing to meet tonight.

160
00:08:44,333 --> 00:08:45,200
Tonight?

161
00:08:46,033 --> 00:08:47,200
Can't that wait until tomorrow?

162
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:50,033
Their schedule just opened up.

163
00:08:50,167 --> 00:08:53,833
If we don't go, they might
give it to a competitor.

164
00:08:54,767 --> 00:08:56,067
That would be a waste.

165
00:08:56,967 --> 00:08:59,133
This could recover all
our losses from last quarter.

166
00:09:01,233 --> 00:09:02,133
Thea...

167
00:09:03,033 --> 00:09:06,833
I promised Marj
I'd be home for dinner.

168
00:09:11,267 --> 00:09:15,900
Then just tell her
you'll be late.

169
00:09:17,333 --> 00:09:18,200
Paolo...

170
00:09:18,867 --> 00:09:20,533
this is business.

171
00:09:21,533 --> 00:09:24,333
This is our only shot
to turn things around.

172
00:09:26,167 --> 00:09:27,967
This used to be her job.

173
00:09:28,133 --> 00:09:29,833
I'm sure she'll understand.

174
00:09:38,567 --> 00:09:40,733
I'll set the meeting
for 7:00 PM.

175
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:47,433
You decide if you're coming.

176
00:10:18,133 --> 00:10:19,300
Marj.

177
00:10:19,733 --> 00:10:23,400
What's with this dinner setup?

178
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,500
It's just dinner, Mom.
A surprise for Paolo.

179
00:10:28,933 --> 00:10:30,433
I just want
to make it up to him.

180
00:10:31,033 --> 00:10:33,800
I know I've been neglecting him
lately.

181
00:10:35,167 --> 00:10:36,767
Wow.

182
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:39,567
Candlelight, wine, petals...

183
00:10:40,933 --> 00:10:42,833
The most overused

184
00:10:43,067 --> 00:10:47,333
desperate-housewife trick
in the book, Marjorie.

185
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:50,867
Why here?

186
00:10:51,633 --> 00:10:53,067
I thought this was
a business meeting.

187
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,733
Not a night out?

188
00:10:56,100 --> 00:10:57,933
The client wanted
to meet here.

189
00:10:59,267 --> 00:11:05,633
He said it's easier to talk
with drinks and ambiance.

190
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:11,267
<i>No matter how hard you try,
if a man's pulling away,</i>

191
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:12,700
<i> he's pulling away.</i>

192
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,933
No matter how hard you try,

193
00:11:15,067 --> 00:11:17,400
if there's already a wall
between you and your husband,

194
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:20,133
it won't be easy
to tear it down.

195
00:11:21,267 --> 00:11:22,467
I know.

196
00:11:23,033 --> 00:11:24,300
I've tried.

197
00:11:40,067 --> 00:11:43,000
You didn't tell me
that this was...

198
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:46,633
this kind of place.

199
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:51,333
Why?

200
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:55,400
You look nervous.

201
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:58,067
Relax, Boss.

202
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:00,900
It's just a meeting. Okay?

203
00:12:02,467 --> 00:12:03,900
Let's get this over with.

204
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:06,200
Marj's waiting for me.

205
00:12:06,933 --> 00:12:08,200
Sure.

206
00:12:09,133 --> 00:12:11,167
Let's just hope
you're not too late

207
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:14,100
getting the client's trust back.

208
00:12:15,767 --> 00:12:17,233
Or Marj's.

209
00:12:33,067 --> 00:12:34,800
Oh, hi, Sir!

210
00:12:41,467 --> 00:12:43,100
Where are you, Love?

211
00:12:43,233 --> 00:12:44,633
<i> Sorry, traffic.</i>

212
00:12:44,767 --> 00:12:46,100
That's okay, no problem.

213
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:47,433
We're just glad you made it.

214
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,400
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

215
00:12:50,533 --> 00:12:51,300
Please, have a seat.

216
00:12:51,433 --> 00:12:53,267
So you're the
husband-and-wife team

217
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:54,767
I've been hearing about.

218
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,167
No, we're not.

219
00:12:58,067 --> 00:13:00,200
His wife is Marj.

220
00:13:00,333 --> 00:13:01,600
I'm Thea Villarreal.

221
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,267
Sorry for assuming.

222
00:13:12,933 --> 00:13:15,067
Looking at you two,
I thought you were together.

223
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,933
Someone had already come
before we met.

224
00:13:30,867 --> 00:13:33,000
We're just very close friends.

225
00:13:33,133 --> 00:13:34,900
We're both taken.

226
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:37,967
He's actually
my future brother-in-law.

227
00:14:09,533 --> 00:14:12,733
I really appreciate you making
the effort to meet me here.

228
00:14:12,867 --> 00:14:15,000
This bar is very important
to me.

229
00:14:15,133 --> 00:14:16,933
This is where I proposed
to my late wife.

230
00:14:17,933 --> 00:14:20,767
If she were still alive,
she'd probably be here with us.

231
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,300
So thank you
for agreeing to meet here.

232
00:14:23,433 --> 00:14:26,133
It shows how much you value
your clients.

233
00:14:26,267 --> 00:14:29,267
Of course. You've always been
one of our top priorities.

234
00:14:30,633 --> 00:14:31,500
Good.

235
00:14:31,633 --> 00:14:32,467
Then we're back in business.

236
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,467
Expect an email
from my team tomorrow.

237
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:35,300
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

238
00:14:35,433 --> 00:14:36,867
Thank you so much, Sir.

239
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:39,167
We won't disappoint you.
That's a promise.

240
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:40,967
Thank you. I'll head out.

241
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:42,200
Thank you.

242
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:47,467
- We did it!
- Yeah!

243
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,333
Finally, some good news!

244
00:14:49,467 --> 00:14:51,733
Hey, give me a high five!

245
00:14:51,867 --> 00:14:53,333
Success!

246
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:00,500
Sorry.

247
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,433
Yeah...

248
00:15:04,967 --> 00:15:05,800
Just be...

249
00:15:08,167 --> 00:15:09,000
careful.

250
00:15:21,467 --> 00:15:22,833
Thank you.

251
00:15:24,567 --> 00:15:26,233
You're welcome.

252
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,833
Maybe we should get going?

253
00:15:43,033 --> 00:15:44,033
Yeah.

254
00:15:45,700 --> 00:15:47,000
So...

255
00:15:49,133 --> 00:15:51,167
Where do you want to go?

256
00:15:59,000 --> 00:15:59,867
No, no.

257
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,933
What I meant was...

258
00:16:02,067 --> 00:16:03,233
I'll drop you off.

259
00:16:03,367 --> 00:16:05,167
At Edward's condo, right?

260
00:16:09,033 --> 00:16:12,500
Excuse me, I'll just call Oscar.

261
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:15,033
You wait here.

262
00:16:28,167 --> 00:16:29,733
- Sir.
- Where's Marj?

263
00:16:29,867 --> 00:16:30,833
She's over there.

264
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:42,867
Love.

265
00:16:44,933 --> 00:16:46,000
Love.

266
00:16:48,367 --> 00:16:49,400
What time is it?

267
00:16:52,067 --> 00:16:54,567
A client meeting
came up suddenly.

268
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:55,700
I'm sorry, Love.

269
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:59,100
Why weren't you
answering my calls?

270
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,000
Did you eat already?

271
00:17:03,133 --> 00:17:04,900
Wait, I'll heat up the food.

272
00:17:05,033 --> 00:17:06,033
Don't.

273
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:07,233
No, it's okay.

274
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:10,433
No, it's okay.

275
00:17:11,767 --> 00:17:13,267
I'd rather just be with you.

276
00:17:15,033 --> 00:17:16,800
I know you're busy.

277
00:17:16,933 --> 00:17:18,200
I just missed you.

278
00:17:29,233 --> 00:17:30,600
Love...

279
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,400
the baby.

280
00:17:36,233 --> 00:17:38,233
Come on, let's go to bed.

281
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:31,533
<i> Relax, Mr. Torrecampo.</i>

282
00:18:32,167 --> 00:18:33,333
<i> Success!</i>

283
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,400
<i> If you can't have it at home,</i>

284
00:18:38,533 --> 00:18:39,900
<i> find it somewhere else.</i>

285
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,267
Love?

286
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:55,633
Love?

287
00:18:56,567 --> 00:18:58,000
<i> Love.</i>

288
00:18:58,500 --> 00:18:59,767
<i> Are you okay in there?</i>

289
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,167
Yes, Love. I'm fine.

290
00:19:04,067 --> 00:19:05,333
<i> I just...</i>

291
00:19:07,033 --> 00:19:08,433
feel kind of hot.

292
00:19:08,567 --> 00:19:11,033
Just give me a minute.
I'll be out.

293
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:15,200
You've been in there a while.

294
00:20:33,767 --> 00:20:34,733
<i> Hon.</i>

295
00:20:37,100 --> 00:20:38,167
<i> Are you okay?</i>

296
00:20:44,967 --> 00:20:47,100
Yeah. I'm fine.

297
00:20:49,933 --> 00:20:51,633
Let's go to sleep?

298
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:05,600
<i> Good news.</i>

299
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:08,967
We're targeting a major client.

300
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:11,600
La Escondida Hotels.

301
00:21:11,733 --> 00:21:14,900
They're building a chain
all over the country.

302
00:21:15,667 --> 00:21:17,333
If we land this,

303
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:21,800
we can recover all our losses
this year.

304
00:21:21,933 --> 00:21:23,167
That's huge, Dad.

305
00:21:23,300 --> 00:21:24,600
Exactly.

306
00:21:24,900 --> 00:21:26,800
That's why you and Thea
are handling it.

307
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:30,267
Us?

308
00:21:31,367 --> 00:21:33,833
Well, it was supposed to be Marj
and Paolo,

309
00:21:33,967 --> 00:21:36,000
but the mom-to-be
is on bed rest.

310
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:40,600
You two did great winning back
our last client.

311
00:21:41,967 --> 00:21:44,933
Looks like you make a good team.

312
00:21:47,267 --> 00:21:48,900
Thank you, Uncle Greg.

313
00:21:49,033 --> 00:21:50,800
We'll do our best
to close the deal.

314
00:21:52,167 --> 00:21:52,967
Good.

315
00:21:53,900 --> 00:21:55,567
I'm sending you there
this Friday.

316
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:57,300
Three days out of town.

317
00:21:57,933 --> 00:22:00,467
Face-to-face with their board.

318
00:22:02,633 --> 00:22:03,700
Good luck.

319
00:22:04,567 --> 00:22:06,933
Dad, that would be the day
after tomorrow.

320
00:22:09,633 --> 00:22:11,467
Business waits for no one, son.

321
00:22:12,733 --> 00:22:15,433
If you want this company
to recover under your watch,

322
00:22:16,833 --> 00:22:18,167
you need momentum.

323
00:22:22,133 --> 00:22:22,900
Well.

324
00:22:24,867 --> 00:22:25,833
Good luck.

325
00:22:28,900 --> 00:22:31,467
Three days out of town.

326
00:22:33,900 --> 00:22:35,333
Sounds like a challenge.

327
00:22:37,367 --> 00:22:40,000
I'm game, if you are.

328
00:23:10,233 --> 00:23:12,800
So you and Thea
have a business trip?

329
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:14,967
It's just three days, right?

330
00:23:16,367 --> 00:23:17,200
Three days.

331
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:20,033
That's dad's directive.

332
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:23,100
Oh, Love, look. It's so cute.

333
00:23:24,967 --> 00:23:26,100
Well, that's nice.

334
00:23:26,233 --> 00:23:28,433
At least it's a change
of scenery.

335
00:23:28,567 --> 00:23:30,333
You've been so stressed
with work.

336
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:32,533
Love...

337
00:23:33,500 --> 00:23:36,133
promise me, when you get back,

338
00:23:36,633 --> 00:23:38,967
we'll spend time together, okay?

339
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:40,833
Before the baby comes.

340
00:23:50,467 --> 00:23:51,767
Of course.

341
00:23:53,133 --> 00:23:56,667
Your due date's still two months
away, right? So we'll have time.

342
00:23:56,833 --> 00:23:58,300
Just the two of us.

343
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:03,600
When you get back, no phones,
no meetings.

344
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:05,067
Just us.

345
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,267
I'm going to miss you, Love.

346
00:24:09,700 --> 00:24:11,267
But I'll manage.

347
00:24:11,833 --> 00:24:13,400
Just come back right away, okay?

348
00:24:14,133 --> 00:24:15,700
No matter what happens,

349
00:24:16,767 --> 00:24:19,100
I'll always come back to you.

350
00:24:28,033 --> 00:24:29,000
So...

351
00:24:29,900 --> 00:24:32,000
A three-day business
trip with Paolo?

352
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:33,767
Are you serious, Thea?

353
00:24:34,333 --> 00:24:35,700
Hon, it's work.

354
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:37,767
Your dad assigned us, remember?

355
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:40,033
Big client. La Escondida.

356
00:24:40,167 --> 00:24:41,233
Why you?

357
00:24:41,667 --> 00:24:43,467
Couldn't someone else go
with him?

358
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:46,233
Because I earned it.

359
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:48,600
Wait, why does it suddenly
bother you so much

360
00:24:48,733 --> 00:24:50,067
whenever I have work stuff
with Pao?

361
00:24:53,500 --> 00:24:56,467
Hon, this is good for my career.

362
00:24:56,767 --> 00:24:58,333
I can't just depend on you

363
00:24:58,467 --> 00:24:59,933
while you're building
that startup

364
00:25:00,067 --> 00:25:01,733
that hasn't even launched yet.

365
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:03,333
So now it's my fault?

366
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:06,267
It's my fault you're working?

367
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:07,300
Thea, I don't need your money,

368
00:25:07,433 --> 00:25:08,867
especially if it's coming
from them.

369
00:25:09,767 --> 00:25:11,000
Relax...

370
00:25:11,533 --> 00:25:12,900
it's not like that.

371
00:25:14,633 --> 00:25:17,767
I'm doing this for my career.

372
00:25:18,633 --> 00:25:20,333
This is part of my job.

373
00:25:21,367 --> 00:25:22,900
It's just three days, okay?

374
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:24,467
Three days.

375
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:06,933
- Hi, Paolo.
- Hi, Thea.

376
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:08,800
Ma'am.

377
00:26:09,100 --> 00:26:11,033
Ma'am, can you grab
Thea's luggage from the back?

378
00:26:11,267 --> 00:26:12,167
Thanks.

379
00:26:14,367 --> 00:26:16,033
Wait, where's the company car?

380
00:26:16,367 --> 00:26:17,900
About that, I canceled it.

381
00:26:18,033 --> 00:26:20,867
I figured Oscar
could just drive us.

382
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:23,600
But Oscar texted me earlier.

383
00:26:23,867 --> 00:26:26,000
He's sick. Can't make it.

384
00:26:26,133 --> 00:26:28,367
Then have the company driver
come here.

385
00:26:28,500 --> 00:26:29,867
I thought of that, too.

386
00:26:30,633 --> 00:26:32,833
But he's coming all the way
from Las Piñas.

387
00:26:33,167 --> 00:26:36,067
If I call him now,
we'll get delayed.

388
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:37,867
- Hold on, let me take this.
- So, how are you getting there?

389
00:26:38,300 --> 00:26:39,533
No choice. I'll drive.

390
00:26:39,667 --> 00:26:40,433
What?

391
00:26:42,833 --> 00:26:43,567
Deja vu.

392
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:45,300
Isn't this how
you two started before?

393
00:26:45,433 --> 00:26:46,333
What did you say?

394
00:26:46,467 --> 00:26:48,500
The road to La Escondida
is actually beautiful.

395
00:26:48,633 --> 00:26:52,267
Feels like the perfect spot
for a breather.

396
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:53,467
What happened?

397
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:55,367
Did the car break down?

398
00:26:55,500 --> 00:26:57,500
Didn't you tell me
if something's broken,

399
00:26:57,633 --> 00:27:00,067
don't just leave it like that?
We should fix it.

400
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:01,967
Marj, you're wet.

401
00:27:02,100 --> 00:27:03,500
Seriously?
Now it starts raining?

402
00:27:03,633 --> 00:27:05,400
I'll find somewhere
we can take cover. Wait!

403
00:27:05,533 --> 00:27:07,567
She needs surgery.

404
00:27:07,700 --> 00:27:09,333
The baby's in distress.

405
00:27:09,467 --> 00:27:10,833
Where's Paolo?

406
00:27:10,967 --> 00:27:12,533
Paolo, where are you?
